# Jira Triage Taxonomy

## Project
- Project key: `WEL`
- Project type: team-managed (next-gen)
- All classification is done via Labels + Priority field + Fix Version
- No native Jira Components — labels carry all structural metadata

---

## Layer Labels (`layer:*`)

Every item must have exactly one `layer:` label.

| Label | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `layer:core` | Foundational system objects. Everything else depends on these. Changes here have the widest blast radius. Includes: Health Thread, Data Factory, State Machine. |
| `layer:infra` | Cross-cutting concerns that touch all layers. Safety model, privacy guardrails, auth. Changes here affect correctness and trust across the system. |
| `layer:feature-backend` | Server-side feature work. Business logic, data processing, persistence. |
| `layer:feature-frontend` | Client-side / UI work. Views, interactions, user-facing flows. |
| `layer:feature-api` | API surface and contracts. Endpoints, schemas, versioning. |
| `layer:feature-integration` | External integrations. Wearables, EHR import, third-party data sources. |

---

