## Impact Radius Labels (`impact:*`)

Every item must have exactly one `impact:` label. Assigned during CLASSIFY step, confirmed during WALK step.

| Label | Meaning | Blast radius implication |
|---|---|---|
| `impact:self-contained` | Change lives entirely within one component. No downstream effects. | Agent acts autonomously. No approval needed. |
| `impact:component-local` | Change affects 1–2 directly linked components. Contained spread. | Agent asks before creating or modifying Epics/Features. |
| `impact:cross-cutting` | Change propagates across multiple layers or components. Wide spread. | Agent presents full triage report and waits for approval before any write. |

**When in doubt, assign the higher impact radius.** It is always safer to over-estimate blast radius.

---

## Priority Tiers (Jira Priority field)

| Value | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `P0-blocker` | Blocks everything else. Must be resolved before any other work proceeds. |
| `P1-critical` | Must ship in the current phase. High risk if deferred. |
| `P2-important` | Should ship in the current phase. Meaningful but not blocking. |
| `P3-backlog` | Tracked, not scheduled. Will be picked up when capacity allows. |

Priority is set on the Jira Priority field, not as a label.

---

## Phase (Fix Version)

Every item targets exactly one Fix Version. Version IDs are fixed for the `WEL` project.

| Version name | ID | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| `mvp` | 10000 | Ships in the minimum viable product |
| `post-mvp` | 10001 | Ships after initial launch |
| `deferred` | 10002 | Explicitly deprioritised — tracked but not scheduled |

---

## Re-evaluation Flag Labels (`re-eval:*`)

Set by the agent during WALK and EXECUTE steps. Never set manually unless explicitly needed.

| Label | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `re-eval:clean` | Item has been reviewed and is consistent with the current system state. |
| `re-eval:needs-review` | Item is in the blast radius of a recent change. Needs review before work starts. |
| `re-eval:blocked-by-change` | Item cannot proceed until a blocking dependency is resolved. |

---

## Triage Session Label

Format: `triage-YYYY-MM-DD-NNN` where NNN is a zero-padded sequence number for that day.

Example: `triage-2026-05-30-001`

Every item created or updated during a triage run must carry this label. The VERIFY step uses it to confirm execution completeness.
